com.siperian.sif.message

Class TaskMetaData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.siperian.sif.message.TaskMetaData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TaskData

    public class TaskMetaData
extends Object
implements Serializable
    A subset of the task object representing only the non-data related fields.

    Required for CreateTaskRequest or UpdateTaskRequest:

    • type
    • subject area
    • title
    • task id - managed by Hub for CreateTaskRequest, required with UpdateTaskRequest

    Optional for CreateTaskRequest or UpdateTaskRequest:

    • due date
    • priority - defaults to 0
    • status - defaults to TaskStatusEnum.OPEN
    • owner
    • interaction id

    Other fields are managed by Hub and cannot be set by user code:

    • task id - required with UpdateTaskRequest
    • workflow process id - required with UpdateTaskRequest
    • create date
    • created by user
    • last update date
    • last updated by user
    • previous owner
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • setInteractionId

        public void setInteractionId(String interactionId)
        Used to protect any pending records associated with this task. Only SIF requests having this same interactionId can update this task. The interactionId can be set either at the request level (see SiperianRequest.setInteractionId(String) for CreateTaskRequest or UpdateTaskRequest) or here.

        Warning: if interactionId is set in both places and conflict, an error will be thrown.
